Abdomen dark brown with white anterior margin and wide longitudinal median band not extending to its end (
Plate 5
). Venter yellow with large triangular dark grey spot. Dense hairs in background colour cover whole abdomen, among them sparse long brown setae. Spinnerets dark. Legs light brown with darker rings, basal parts of femora yellow. First pair in some specimens dark brown. Spines numerous, brownish. Pedipalps yellowish brown. Bulb rounded, single tibial apophysis short, obtuse on its tip (
Fig. 14
